text:
i think about this day everyday, and dread it as it comes closer. i try avoid everything that this day has done but at the end of the day i live with it and wear it like an article of clothing. it's been 5 years and i still live with the effects of its wrath, but today i found some strength to look this demon in the face; though, i couldn't manage to leave my car i still came. to some it would look like a park but to me it's a place that my life turned upside down. someday i will look at it as just a park or just a place that holds memory but this is the first step toward that. i owe it to 17 year old me to be strong, happy, healthy, and worthy of love. 
#metoo #endthestigma #surviving

text:
#rkelly #justice #helpwomen r. kelly was charged with multiple counts of criminal sexual abuse in a chicago court friday after decades of rumors and allegations that the r&b star was abusing women and underage girls.

tandra simonton, spokeswoman for the cook county state's attorney's office, confirmed to the associated press the charges had been filed against the 52-year-old grammy winner but declined to say the specific number. media reports said there were 10 counts, at least some involving an underage victim or victims.

michael avenatti: r. kelly seen having sex with underage girl in newly uncovered video

kelly has denied allegations of sexual misconduct involving women and underage girls for decades. neither kelly’s legal representative nor the cook county prosecutor's office immediately responded to fox news’ request for comment on the charges.

the singer, whose full name is robert kelly, is one of the top-selling recording artists of all time. he has won multiple grammys, including for his hit song, "i believe i can fly." his arrest sets the stage for another #metoo-era celebrity trial after bill cosby went to prison last year, and former hollywood studio boss harvey weinstein is awaiting trial.

i asked a friend if they’d picked a wedding hashtag yet. he said yeah, #metoo
...
are you fucking kidding me? i don’t have the energy today to talk about how making jokes like this perpetuates rape culture—how it normalizes men assaulting women and belittles our movement. i don’t have the energy to talk about how when one guy makes a joke like that in front of other guys—he’s validating the rapist in the group (because there is almost certainly at least one). ...
and tell me, what does it say when you make that joke to someone who talks openly about how deeply sexual assault has impacted her and how it continues to haunt her?
...
a few days ago, in the midst of a fiery conversation about the female experience, my husband had the nerve to say, “i hope you won’t always be so angry about this.”
...
i turned slowly, like a movie character, to face him. “then you better get your ass in the streets and start working for real change, because until things are radically different, i’m going to be angry.”
...
do better, gentlemen. you have got to do better.

⠀⠀
i learned recently at a workshop with @zabie.yamasaki , that individuals with a history of trauma can have a really challenging time looking within, because it feels really unsafe to do so.
⠀⠀
i appreciate all the new insight i received with modifications and choices for mindfulness, and i also know there are a variety of other challenges you might be facing with meditation.
⠀⠀
what are they for you?

text:
israel’s not your toy “life is big, but i like my jewelry even bigger!” is a perfect introductory quote from liat ginzberg, israel's trendiest and bold jewelry designer. we first connected years ago at bijoux at the norton museum of art. the yearly event hosts several top israeli jewelry designers and is chaired by none other than my second mom, donna schneier. since i am a big jewelry fan in every sense of the word big, i immediately gravitated towards liat's collection. over the years we have formed a great friendship and she has customized an assortment of pieces for me that are bold, big, beautiful and brazen. perfectly suited for the occasions as new york fashion week or tv appearances in which my accessories need to say a lot! 
liat has grown over the years to include a multitude of vogue editorials, but her current most famous admirer is the israeli singing sensation netta . the marriage of liat and netta is perfect. they are both an outrageous example of self love and patriotism. neither one shrinks to accommodate anyone who thinks otherwise. of course i'll explain my statement. 
liat ginzberg's jewelry are daring, one of a kind pieces with their abundant use of color and electrifying style. the designs express a nostalgic yet current view on the 90`s club scene combined with hints of frida khalo, carmen meranda, lucille ball and madonna. 
each piece is composed of vintage elements from the 70`s and the 80`s, which liat collects on her travels around the world. all these elements and influences produce a perfectly unique style that is all her own. liat never compromises to trends, she remains herself in each earring, bracelet and necklace. 
netta , born netta barzilai, winner of eurovision 2018, approached the music scene with a huge entrance. her song toy became an anthem for the #metoo movement as well as an international number 1 hit. “barzilai's style might not be everyone's cup of tea, but her carnival-like appearance is an antithesis of the demand placed on israeli artists to shrink, appear nonchalant and not draw too much attention to themselves.” says ynet news. @nettabarzi @liatginzburg @ynetgram @queensjewishlink @queensjewishlink
name: Tobi Rubinstein
tweet_full:
israel’s not your toy “life is big, but i like my jewelry even bigger!” is a perfect introductory quote from liat ginzberg, israel's trendiest and bold jewelry designer. we first connected years ago at bijoux at the norton museum of art. the yearly event hosts several top israeli jewelry designers and is chaired by none other than my second mom, donna schneier. since i am a big jewelry fan in every sense of the word big, i immediately gravitated towards liat's collection. over the years we have formed a great friendship and she has customized an assortment of pieces for me that are bold, big, beautiful and brazen. perfectly suited for the occasions as new york fashion week or tv appearances in which my accessories need to say a lot! 
liat has grown over the years to include a multitude of vogue editorials, but her current most famous admirer is the israeli singing sensation netta . the marriage of liat and netta is perfect. they are both an outrageous example of self love and patriotism. neither one shrinks to accommodate anyone who thinks otherwise. of course i'll explain my statement.

text:
in 2 weeks im moving back to san diego.  when i first lived in socal, i was a 32 year old in the midst of battling for my mental health.  just a few months prior to my move, i began getting treatment for cptsd.  my nervous breakdown was the simplest scary moment i’ve known and i moved to socal to escape my past life. .
.
i hated living there.  i felt alone.  i felt isolated. i felt terrified of what went on in my mind and body.  i took that out on san diego, and left as soon as i could. .
.
last summer i went back for a last minute visit and by the end of the weekend was overflowing with the amount of love that had been poured into me and the words that displayed how much i was cared for.  it was way more than i knew, i just couldn’t see it. .
.
so, now i return.  i return to the walks along the tide, and the sunsets that hit the ocean so intently that you can’t tell where the water ends and the sky begins.  i return to the many who saw i was hurting and felt restless on how to help me. i return as a very whole, strong, healthy man who is determined to make a difference in other people lives, because wrestling with mental health is a lonely path. .
.
so, today i say to you:  when was the last time you daydreamed about your hardest chapter being over? what do you need to hear today to know without a shadow of a doubt, that your pain has an ending place and the journey of resolution is around the corner? .
.
please accept this as a big virtual hug.... to you! you, the one struggling and feeling overwhelmed.  you, the one holding on because your honesty is not accepted in your environment.  you, because you need to know you are seen and known... you are!! and, you are loved too!!
.
.
keep fighting your battle....xoxo
.
.

text:
r. kelly was charged friday with 10 counts of aggravated criminal sexual abuse on friday morning in cook county, illinois.

a cook county judge then approved an arrest warrant for charges on friday afternoon, the chicago sun-times first reported. 
the r&b superstar has faced nearly two decades of accusations of sexual abuse. and last thursday, cook county prosecutors reportedly received a 45-minute videotape that is said to show kelly performing multiple sex acts with an underage girl, whom both kelly and the girl describe on tape as being 14 years old. 
celebrity lawyer michael avenatti said he turned over the tape to the cook county state’s attorney office. “my client knows the identity of the girl and r. kelly. he identified the two of them on the videotape,” avenatti told cnn last week. “he worked for and has known r. kelly for decades and he met the girl on a number of occasions.” moments before the friday charges were announced, avenatti ominously tweeted: ‘it’s over.’ the singer has repeatedly denied all accusations against him. “[kelly] never knowingly had sex with an underage woman, he never force anyone to do anything, he never held anyone captive, he never abuse anyone,” his lawyer, steve greenberg, told the associated press last month. get the full details and keep up at www.itskenbarbie.com #rkelly #robertkelly #muterkelly #metoo #trappedinthecloset #survivingrkelly #entertainment #lifetime #lifetimetv #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text:
maybe not me too,
maybe my skirt was too short
and my shirt was too tight,
maybe i did drink too much,
and i didn’t say no loud enough.
maybe i thought i was clear,
but maybe you didn’t quite hear.
maybe my screams were whispers
and maybe the taste of my lips said kiss her,
maybe i didn’t fight,
maybe my mind was on flight
maybe not me too,
but why am i nauseous just at the thought of you? 
why is this the accepted point of view?
why not me too?

text:
▪️долой носки.

для покупки носков не нужен праздничный день.

наших мужчин любим и уважаем, выбираем достойные подарки.

леди, позаботьтесь о стиле мужчин и выберете достойную пару к их ногам👣

важно сделать свой выбор в пользу только кожаной и качественной обуви.

так как праздник «на носу» представляю вашему вниманию варианты покупок в магазинах, разные по характеру и образу жизни.

покупая, кожаные мокасины с принтом миллитари, помните, они  не для бойцов, исключительно для креативных личностей и кто от природы чувствует колористику😉

а дальше вы разберётесь про кого красные кеды, а кому в чёрных лоферах с утра в офис 🖋

ставьте ➕ если носки ждут завтрашнего часа😉

though not one of crichton's best (it starts off slow and at times gets bogged down in technical exposition), it's still a great read.

text:
🚨 real talk post 🚨
the bitter truth
i know, i knoooow already... my body only allows me to do one big thing a day. i must’ve thought i was superwoman 🦸🏻‍♀️ or something yesterday, cuz i was feeling particularly good and wanted to take my kids out in the afternoon. we went to 3 places and had just the best time! 🥰👦🏻👧🏻 no, i didn’t forget it was errands night too that day. but when my muscles buckled in the middle of trader joe’s, it was the sudden annoying reminder that i did too much. 🙄😤😏 it’s my harsh reality and something i stubbornly have to accept. 😔
—
what does this have to do with nova? she will never put my limitations against me. 🐶♥️🤕
—

text:
såg i @sophiabush story att denna podcast ägnat ett avsnitt åt rapporteringen kring ryan adams beteende mot kvinnor och unga tjejmusiker/artister. och började direkt lyssna.
att bara höra om hur han hade kontakt med en tjej när hon var i femtonårs åldern. med ett återkommande mönster där allt börjar med prat om musikindustrin och att vara musiker, om hur han kan ”vägleda” och ”ge möjligheter”, ger genast obehagliga vibbar. när han senare själv i deras kommunikation tar upp hur ingen kan få reda på att de har kontakt, med referenser till r.kelly. så vet man ju att han själv vet att det är fel. men fortsätter.
när hon just fyllt 16 och han 40 så hade de en ”sexting” relation online enligt rapporteringen. the new york times reportrar har tagit del av tusentals meddelanden mellan den unga tjejen och adams. som adams själv tydligen inte minns mycket av enligt hans advokat. annat än att han bara pratat musik med de han haft kontakt med.
.
.

posted @withrepost • @sallycredence girls will be...a mother-daughter love story about a sexually curious teen and her anxious mom discover the value of trust and how to break the cycle.

residing in a fictional small, conservative town in indiana, annie wants to explore her sexuality. grace baxter wants to protect her daughter from the high-stakes that comes with being female. when annie's caught making out with her boyfriend, grace's past comes to the surface and the mother-daughter roller coaster begins. grace must reckon with her haunting memories of sex, abortion, and expectations of women prior to the #metoo movement, while annie gets answers for why her mom's such a tight-ass. after all, it's just sex...isn't it? #writingcommunity #womensupportwomen #womenempowerment #womenwriters #prochoice #metoo #sexeducation #reproductiverights #plannedparenthood #parenting #motherhood #opencommunication

text:
this workshop & support group is for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the psychological and energetic imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. •

within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways.
•

in session 2, we will: ✨assess how we may re-create trauma in our lives
✨identify ways to reclaim our safety
✨identify how to listen to our bodies to better control our responses to triggers
✨learn ways to process emotions
✨establish a clear connection between the emotions and physical body responses
✨learn new destressing techniques

rsvp at iamthecreatress.com/ourevents 💕
•
•

text:
join @iamthecreatress in this workshop & support group for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the psychological and energetic imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. •

within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways.
•

in session 2, we will: ✨assess how we may re-create trauma in our lives
✨identify ways to reclaim our safety
✨identify how to listen to our bodies to better control our responses to triggers
✨learn ways to process emotions
✨establish a clear connection between the emotions and physical body responses
✨learn new destressing techniques

rsvp at iamthecreatress.com/ourevents 💕
•
•

text:
epistémè, as popularised by the philosopher foucault, relates to the ideas that shape our perception of reality within a particular period.
this is the title of our latest collection, inspired as it is by feminism and movements such as #metoo that are defining our current reality.
the words of simone de beauvoir found within our jewelry collection, albeit taken from another generation, completely resonate in the context of
today’s society.
tailoring, deconstruction and art are a constant inspiration in our collections.
epistémè, término popularizado por el filósofo foucault, se relaciona con las ideas que dan forma a nuestra percepción acerca de la realidad de acuerdo a período en particular.
éste es el título de nuestra más reciente colección, inspirada en el feminismo y movimientos como #metoo que definen nuestra realidad actualmente.
las frases feministas de simone de beauvoir en nuestra colección de joyería, aunque son frases escritas durante el siglo pasado siguen siendo actuales en el contexto de nuestra sociedad hoy día.  la sastrería, la deconstrucción y el arte, son una constante inspiración en cada una de nuestras colecciones.

text: this is where it all began. i originally self-published the princess saves herself in this one 3 years ago, thinking no one would ever want to read my story, which largely revolves around my experience with child abuse, mental illness, & grief. i was shocked to learn that so many people not only wanted to read it but even found themselves reflected in its pages. the overwhelming support you showed the princess helped her become a traditionally published book with @andrewsmcmeel, a bestseller, as well as a @goodreads award-winner. then somewhere in the whirlwind, i decided it needed to be the first in a series where i tell my truths. now, 3 years later, the last book is about to be released into the world, & it tells a story i never thought i would be able to tell. you—yes, you—make me feel brave enough to tell it & for that i owe you an infinity of thanks. i’ll see you on march 5th with the mermaid’s voice returns in this one!!! 💜🧜🏻‍♀️ #metoo

text_retweet:
tgif people😍. back on ig, this was the post that popped up and thought to share.
.
.thank you @healingherco for sharing this👏🏼
.
.reposted from @healingherco -  feel your feels.

since our deepest traumas are imbedded in our guts and muscles, to free ourselves we must free our bodies. -

from infancy we are fed ideas of what strength is... "toughen up", "keep it together", "get over it". when we cut ourselves off from fully feeling it's like slamming on the gas and breaks at the same time.  this is one example of how illness can manifest in our bodies. -

on the deepest level, change always involves the body. - - take a moment to ask where these uncomfortable feelings live in your body? - - acknowledge and thank them for their positive intentions. - - soften your body, breathe, and let yourself feel.

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
film review - “the house that jack built” (2018) lars von trier (tap for sound)
————————————————
tribute to bruno ganz (1941-2019)
————————————————
the way i see it, there are two types of films about characters who commit various immoral acts; those which try to make us feel pity or forgive the character to a degree such as “american beauty” or “lolita” and there are those which want us to be disgusted and hate the character. “the house that jack built” is most definitely the latter. 
failed architect and vicious sociopath, jack retells his malicious acts in five randomly chosen acts which he calls ‘incidents’. each incident is extremely visceral and leaves nothing to the imagination. in most films with heavy violence the violence is usually implied but not shown, von trier didn’t do this though, no, the camera captures each horrific scene fully. 
out of the five incidents the most horrific and vile is the third incident in which jack murders a single mother and their two sons before using rigor mortis, sticks and wire to turn one of the boys into taxidermy. 
on the relatively lighter side of things, jack’s second act is darkly comic as he fails to strangle a suspicious old woman before stabbing her. after hours of cleaning up, his ocd forces him to second guess himself and look over every nook and cranny multiple times. just when he’s about to leave, a police officer arrives at the house. jack feeds the officer some lies and is on his merry way. to add to jack’s hilarious comedy of errors, the lady’s body leaves a bloody trail all the way back to jack’s storage freezer. as he realises this it begins to rain and wash away the trail. jack calls this a “miracle from god” much to his escort, virgil’s dismay. 
well that’s just what is on the surface of the film, really the film is a big ‘fuck you’ from von trier to liberal complainers. he even casts uma thurman (a #metoo advocate) as a stupid, irritating woman who has it coming to her. i also think that von trier is trying to use the shock factor of ‘the house that jack built’ as a way of expressing how liberal modern cinema is. 
an excellent film and definitely one of my favourites from 2018. 9.5/10.

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it’s why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading – which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs – and he listened to wylie’s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge’s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans.
.
- in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it’s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
long post alert
_______

it would be factual to say that most days i don't feel "hot". actually i'm usually in sweat paints covered in food splatters from cooking or wax from crafts. this, however, was not one of those days. on this day, i was really feeling myself. i got several compliments that really tried to stroke my ego. 
_______

what you don't see is that just a week prior, i had one of the most stressful and pressing times of last year. i lost my best friend, and was in an uncomfortable situation with another close one. i was dealing with some heavy family things and it was just like things weren't aligning the way that i thought they would. 
________

the point is this, never look at the outer appearance and make assumptions about people. things in real life sometimes appear the way they do on social media: like everything is perfect, but it can be far from it. don't let people or social media blindly fool you into thinking that your life, career, purpose, or position are not where they should be and that their lifestyle is much greater. work hard in whatever it is that you do, be better than you were yesterday, and spread love to all that come on your path. 
_______

i'm thankful for those experiences, because they have brought me here: healthy, happy and whole. i've gained peace, wisdom, joy and understanding from those experiences, so when you see me, i still may have on those stain filled sweats, but know this... i'm good.

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
depression, here you are again. this is a poem i wrote recently (link in bio), and published on medium.⁣⁣
✍🏻⁣⁣
⁣⁣
i’ve been opening up more about my long and difficult journey with #depression. can i be honest with you?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
this is so freaking hard to admit.⁣⁣
🤦🏻‍♀️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
even as i write this...my eyes well up with tears, and i have to battle the negative self talk.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
- what will people think of me?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
- i’m not good enough.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
- who am i to help anyone, when sometimes i can’t get out of my own way?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
anyway. the truth is, if it was only for me, i wouldn’t share. it would be easier to put on my mask –– hide from the world –– and pretend i’ve always got it together.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
but, i feel god guiding me to share in my suffering.⁣⁣
✨⁣⁣
⁣⁣
perhaps by doing so, it will help another brave soul shine their light.⁣
⁣
(photo credit: asdrubal luna on unsplash)

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

writer: @kathryn.mcauliffe⁣
media: @mariaberni_⁣
us sailor, george mendonsa, who was famously photographed the day wwii ended kissing a stranger, greta zimmer friedman, passed away monday. the famous picture was erected into a statue called “unconditional surrender” in sarasota, florida that was vandalized with the words “#metoo” the day after mendonsa’s death.  in light of the waves the #metoo movement has made, many have suggested the photo pictures sexual assault, not romantic bliss. ms. zimmer did not know mr. mendonsa at the time and in a 2005 interview for the veterans history project she said that mr. mendonsa grabbed her. ms. zimmer reassured however that she saw the kiss as a “jubilant act.” the city removed the graffiti yet many have called for the statue to be taken down. ⁣

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
do you feel stuck or unable to be successful in pretty much anything you try? weight, salary, your relationship, even your daily to do list let alone your 5 year goals?!? do you often ask, ‘what am i doing wrong? why can’t i have this for myself?’ do you ever feel completely deflated and frustrated with your lack of living? you’ve put the schooling in, you have checked all the boxes, now you’re waiting. when the fuck does life start? am i right? .
i used to be right there with you. and the guilt for not being able to appreciate the blessings i do have was overwhelming. i often wondered what is wrong with me. is it just me who feels this way? .
coaching woke me up. i put the work into my mindset and began to develop gratitude for everything i had. i started to see the joy in the small things. i started reshaping the problems in my life to be opportunity based and not outcome based. i started living. coaching isn’t just about fitness for me. it’s about learning how to be happy after 30yrs of reaching. it’s about connecting to a greater purpose. it’s about helping yourself so you can serve others. when you reshape your mind everything else lines up. the universe works in amazing ways and if you haven’t yet started to open your eyes to that, you need to. join me in this amazing journey of abundance. .
.
we start march 4th. drop your email without .com below to join. .
flexible fitness | nutrition | meal plans | 1:1 coach | growth
.
.
ps i’m 18m postpartum from my 2nd 9lb baby, 3 pregnancies, miscarriage survivor, sexual assault survivor, graduated with 104k in debt in the 2008 recession and still find joy in life. you can too. .
.
.
@sharonbdaleyfit @tiredasamothaa  @dawnsadler83 @amy_eames_fitness @aegood85 @magdawrites @life_aswecallit

text:
#bgb - a north texas teenager who falsely claimed she was kidnapped and raped by three black men last march will likely serve no prison time.

on thursday, 19-year-old breana harmon of pottsboro pleaded guilty to four felony charges of tampering with physical evidence and government documents in relation to false reports of kidnapping and sexual assault. “she’s very remorseful for what she did and what she said, and that’s why she decided to plead guilty,” harmon’s attorney bob jarvis told the sherman herald democrat. no suspects were ever identified or arrested in the case.

harmon will be sentenced march 20. her plea deal has two possible punishments: regular probation or deferred adjudication, which often involves fulfilling a requirement, such as treatment or community service. neither involves prison time.  #firstthem #themfirst #metoo #freebillcosby #jussiesmollett

text:
{werbung-unbezahlt} eine sehr wichtige geschlechtsspezifische studie über die youtuber*innen, hier einige überschriften davon: 
a) frauen sind auf youtube deutlich unterrepräsentiert

b) sie zeigen sich vor allem mit formaten und themen, die als stereotyp weiblich gelten

c) männliche youtuber sind mit einem breiteren themenfeld für die nutzer*innen sichtbar und bedienen mehr genres

d) während männer ihre tätigkeit eher als professionelles können de- klarieren, stellen frauen ihr handeln häufi- ger als hobby dar

e) frauen agieren meist im privaten umfeld, während männer oft den öffentlichen raum als kulisse nutzen

f) frauen inszenieren sich emotionaler als ihre männlichen kollegen, indem sie häufiger ihre eigenen gefühle thematisieren 
g) ... h) ... i) ... in dieser studie wurden insgesamt 1000 youtube-kanäle und 2000 videos analysiert und viele interviews mit youtuberinnen geführt.
das ergebnis: eine #propaganda maschine für die #reproduktion von klassischen und sexistischen geschlechtszuschreibungen!!!#stoppt den digitalen sexismus! #digitalesexismus
#malisastiftung #kapitalismus 
#geschlechtergerechtigkeit #weiblich #sexismus #metoo #yes2no #frauennotrufhannover #youtube #youtubers #queer

text:
i was in one of the darkest places in my adult life 4 1/2 years ago. ⁣
⁣
we had some tragic events hit our household that sent our little family into financial, physical and emotional turmoil on top of my already overwhelmed mental state being 6 months postpartum. ⁣
⁣
then enter this kit.⁣
⁣
i had no idea what oils even where when my friend joanna sent me this kit but i soon realized that these little bottles were life changing. ⁣
⁣
you see, this kit launched an incredible series of events that have bettered our life every since. ⁣
⁣
i felt an emotional weight lifted just within the first week of using this kit. i can’t even explain the relief i felt. ⁣
⁣
without this kit i never would have been sent down the path of living a more natural life for our family. ⁣
⁣
less chemicals, less toxins, less hassle. ⁣
⁣
when i got my kit i swore i wouldn’t do the  business side...we can all laugh at that now. 😂⁣
the hard work that resulted in financial freedom within an incredible community for a company like none other...the best! ⁣
⁣
but more importantly i truly believe without the kit and all of the above i wouldn’t be here right now...on this deep spiritual journey, connecting to my soul like never before, experiencing bliss and healing that’s sometimes indescribable. 😭⁣
⁣
this kit opened me up to a different way of thinking and living. outside of the box if you will. ⁣
⁣
so if you’re looking for a new way to do things in life and haven’t got your kit yet, i urge you to check it out. i’d love to help you but if you don’t sign up with me, be sure and find someone that knows their stuff, can educate you, get you plugged into groups & resources, and has an incredible community to join! ♥️♥️♥️⁣
⁣
#lifechanging ⁣
⁣

text:
words play a powerful role in oppression. the #metoo movement by #taranaburke clarified a lot for me. i had internalized over 40 years-worth of demeaning words. 
these seemingly innocuous words had been a factor in lowering my self-esteem… in stifling my voice when i had something important to say… in keeping me from questioning the power structures in place… in keeping me…quiet.

if these words have had such a stronghold over my life – a privileged cis-gender white woman – what effect have they had over more marginalized individuals? i will never fully understand the extent, but it’s my mission to empathize and act. and it makes me extremely angry.

so go ahead, call me an angry woman. i am angry. finally. and if you’re not already, you should be too. -------
photos by @maria.font.photography

text:
each of these women you can see in the picture carry a story not everybody has the strength to listen to. 
after covering on foot 10,000 kilometers, spread over 24 states in 200 districts of india, this entourage of over five thousand rape survivors concluded the garima yatra/dignity march today. sharing their stories of assault along the way, they raised their voices loud enough to reach every nook and corner. amongst them were women who were raped in front of their children, women who were abducted, abused and left to bleed, women who were branded as witches by fellow villagers when they reported their assault, women who were beaten up by their families for getting abused, women who were left by their husbands, women who were raped because they belong to a lower caste, women who were raped because they tried to stop another women/girl child from being abused, women who now are mothers to their rapist's child, women who are now jobless, aimless and awfully hurt, men who lost their daughters and sisters to a sexual assault. 
each of these stories is worth an instagram post, worth a hashtag, worth a blog, yet each of these stories is so horrifying that you can barely have courage to listen to them. 
while urban women or women with access to social media reported their abuses with the #metoo  movement, these uneducated and underprivileged women sought to traditional means in order to be heard. while they might have concluded their journey, it is on us, the citizens to not let their voices fade away. 
this post is a simple reminder that an abuse is an abuse even if it didn't happen in front of your eyes, a survivor is a survivor even if she/he is not related to you, a person who reports her/his assault deserves to be heard and to be supported no matter whether she/he does so via a social media account or via a rural self help group.

#womensmarch #womenempowerment #womenunite #storiesofabuse #survivornotavictim #womenpower #sexualabuse #womensupportwomen #dignitymarch #garimayatra #metooindia #sexualharassment #sexualassault #lifeasweknowit #deathasweknowit #igdaily @shespeaksforthechange
@indianwomenblog @womensmarch @miss_matured @women.slogans

tweet_full:
each of these women you can see in the picture carry a story not everybody has the strength to listen to. 
after covering on foot 10,000 kilometers, spread over 24 states in 200 districts of india, this entourage of over five thousand rape survivors concluded the garima yatra/dignity march today. sharing their stories of assault along the way, they raised their voices loud enough to reach every nook and corner. amongst them were women who were raped in front of their children, women who were abducted, abused and left to bleed, women who were branded as witches by fellow villagers when they reported their assault, women who were beaten up by their families for getting abused, women who were left by their husbands, women who were raped because they belong to a lower caste, women who were raped because they tried to stop another women/girl child from being abused, women who now are mothers to their rapist's child, women who are now jobless, aimless and awfully hurt, men who lost their daughters and sisters to a sexual assault. 
each of these stories is worth an instagram post, worth a hashtag, worth a blog, yet each of these stories is so horrifying that you can barely have courage to listen to them. 
while urban women or women with access to social media reported their abuses with the #metoo  movement, these uneducated and underprivileged women sought to traditional means in order to be heard. while they might have concluded their journey, it is on us, the citizens to not let their voices fade away. 
this post is a simple reminder that an abuse is an abuse even if it didn't happen in front of your eyes, a survivor is a survivor even if she/he is not related to you, a person who reports her/his assault deserves to be heard and to be supported no matter whether she/he does so via a social media account or via a rural self help group.

#womensmarch #womenempowerment #womenunite #storiesofabuse #survivornotavictim #womenpower #sexualabuse #womensupportwomen #dignitymarch #garimayatra #metooindia #sexualharassment #sexualassault #lifeasweknowit #deathasweknowit #igdaily @shespeaksforthechange
@indianwomenblog @womensmarch @miss_matured @women.slogans

text:
a north texas teenager who falsely claimed she was kidnapped and raped by three black men last march will likely serve no prison time.

on thursday, 19-year-old breana harmon of pottsboro pleaded guilty to four felony charges of tampering with physical evidence and government documents in relation to false reports of kidnapping and sexual assault. “she’s very remorseful for what she did and what she said, and that’s why she decided to plead guilty,” harmon’s attorney bob jarvis told the sherman herald democrat. no suspects were ever identified or arrested in the case.

harmon will be sentenced march 20. her plea deal has two possible punishments: regular probation or deferred adjudication, which often involves fulfilling a requirement, such as treatment or community service. neither involves prison time.  #firstthem #themfirst #metoo #freebillcosby #jussiesmollett

on the blog: less than human: non-consensual sex in a relationship (link in bio)⠀
⠀
here we go... so this piece sat in a journal for years untouched. at the time that's what i wanted, out of my brain and on paper in a dusty book under my bed, forgotten.

a big reason i didn't want to share this was that i’ve always been scared of appearing weak. i‘m uncomfortable in my vulnerability but i've come to realize that there is also a lot of strength in being vulnerable.⠀
⠀
i published this piece quietly on another online publication last year and only shared it with a small group because i didn’t want people looking at me differently. i didn’t want anyone to pity me, to feel sorry for me or worse, to think i was broken because i’m not.⠀
⠀
what i went through should never ever happen to anyone but it has made me a stronger person who can hopefully help others.⠀
⠀
b xo⠀
⠀

text:
with what i’m about to say, i don’t exactly know how to put my feelings into words. i am speaking out for the first time about an assult that was perputrated against me on february 6, 2019. 
it was a fucking nightmare. i was violated, verbally abused and drugged.
this was not done by just any stranger or sketchy hook up, this was a friend that i’ve known for 5 years. this came out of nowhere & he held me against my will.
i thought he cared about me as a friend and person. 
i tried to reach my friends that night, i got one. he then lied to that friend of mine saying i was okay and things were fine. i was not at ease, i was not fine. 
at some point in the night he hid his charger so i wouldn’t be able to charge my phone so i could leave. my phone ended up dying. he took my clothes off and shaved my entire body, including my private parts. he then called me names like retarded, handicapped, stupid, white trash and faggot. i felt all i can do is just take it and wait until it’s over.
i feel like i’ve been stripped down on every level. i am trying to find myself again, i don’t think i’ll be able to date anytime soon after this trauma i endured. i keep crying off and on. i feel ugly right now; physically and mentally.  i do not wish him harm, i hope he gets the help that he needs and i hope his soul can change for the best. 
i don’t want to feel uncomfortable nor unsafe going to friends houses, club and bars; especially in the lgbt community.
i should only feel safe and welcomed. 
i have reported this crime to police, and i am getting the help i need. i know speaking out will not take the pain away but i want people to understand this can happen to anybody. you are not alone. you are strong. 
please remember to stay safe. 
#metoo
#mentoo

text: anyone that knows me, knows that i let my heart run my decisions, my life, my direction for the day for every day for the month for everything!! this here reminds me that even though following my heart has led me to heartbreak, to pain, to doubt and many other things that make me question my strength... to let your heart lead the way is to be an extremely strong person! because you are smart enough to know that there could be other ways, smarter ways, but believing in others, in faith in miracles in anything and everything that will just make life a bit better is all worth it! and that takes being strong in preparing for disappointment, sadness, pain you name it.. but it’s all worth it in the end. that experience that someone that event is molding you to be the person you are meant to be in this life! i am laura sanchez!! i have been through the worst in life.. death was what i saw as my only way out of the pain i carried and i realized there’s more to life than that. i still think and let my heart lead the way. and will continue to do so! happy friday friends!!! i hope y’all have a wonderful day today and everyday! smile!!! make someone’s day! here’s my smile to y’all 😬😬😬 thanks for the quote love! @alee_saldana_ #lifequotes #life #women #strongwomen #houston #live #liveandlearn #love #loveyourself #metoo #strength #motivate #pushyourself #houston #heart #itsok #heart #strongheart #letyourheartguideyou

text:
sophie kahn, machines for suffering xii: blueprint ii, 2018, framed archival chromogenic print on hahnemuhle museum etching paper with watercolor, 17 x 22in. 
_______________ 
don’t miss transfigured, featuring the work of sophie kahn, gabriel barcia-colombo, jaishri abichandani, and andrea dezsö, before it closes on saturday, february 23rd. 
_______________
working from a background in photography and art history, the artist’s post-photographic work sets her in dialogue with the history of medical photography and its impact on the development of photographic technology. kahn’s interest in exposing the way technology fails to capture life starkly contrasts with the 19th century belief that photography was a means of capturing and presenting a “medical truth.” with a title alluding to a quote by pablo picasso, “women are machines for suffering,” said to his mistress françoise gilot, the series offers a potent statement about the production and consumption of female anguish, especially relevant in the time of #metoo.
______________
“i think there’s a lot of concern in the crafts about ‘de-skilling,’ and that digital is taking over from traditional tools. for me, it’s actually been the opposite. digital was my path to learning how to sculpt and learning how to make molds and how to learn physical sculpture tools.” - sophie kahn
_______________
machines for suffering xii: blueprint ii will be on view at c24 gallery for transfigured through february 23rd.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

“i think there’s a lot of concern in the crafts about ‘de-skilling,’ and that digital is taking over from traditional tools. for me, it’s actually been the opposite. digital was my path to learning how to sculpt and learning how to make molds and how to learn physical sculpture tools.” - sophie kahn
_______________
machines for suffering xii: blueprint ii will be on view at c24 gallery for transfigured through february 23rd.

text:
time magazine named the #metoo movement its ‘person’ of the year, highlighting the role companies and nondisclosure agreements play in keeping the victims of abuse silent. 
the city of san antonio texas has been confronted with sexual allegation cases, by comments & touching have recently surfaced. the number of victims who’ve reported being sexually harassed has gone up ever since the metoo movement started, in the year immediately following, there were 16 sexual harassment investigations; almost double over the previous year.”having a greater number doesn’t mean more is happening,” said san antonio city manager, sheryl sculley. “it means that more people are reporting the activity.”in 2018, a female city employee filed a complaint that a senior equipment operator at the city had been making inappropriate comments of a sexual nature for 20 years and also that she had reached the breaking point. city officials believe that employers have brushed off complaints in the past; but that too, is changing.  #kevinlandau #thelandaugroup

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
i have so many mixed opinions about the controversy and critique that has followed #karllagerfeld’s death. is it right to laud a man who was a bigot, racist, cringeworthy in the way he spoke against #metoo and plus-size women ... ... but was also a genius, creating experiences with fashion shows, balancing his ethos between three heavyweight brands (chanel, fendi, karl), power player. there were rocket launches in his shows, faux beaches, icebergs, enchanted forests, casinos, airports, shopping centres, protest marches, doll houses, underwater worlds... you can’t deny the callousness of his comments but you also can’t deny his genius. and even if, like me, you’ve merely been a karl aficionado via the far reaches of the internet, you can’t deny that his death is a severe loss to fashion. 
but yes, it is also a ‘gain’ for the world at large. in a world that is more aware, power players like karl can’t be allowed to air out their bigotry with such pride. they set a precedent that could alarmingly be followed by so many others. 
for better and for worse, there can be no one like lagerfeld. 
#rememberingkarllagerfeld #thegoodthebadtheuglytheveryugly (images via @gettyimages)

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

uma empresa holandesa desenvolveu um aplicativo que oferece um "contrato" de consentimento explícito para o sexo. 
___
segundo o site do app legal fling, a ideia é oferecer aos usuários a possibilidade e a segurança de "estabelecer as regras antes da brincadeira" e deixar claro o que o parceiro e a parceira fariam ou não fariam na cama. 
___
os desenvolvedores partiram do conceito de que o acordo sobre os limites da relação sexual deveriam ser a norma nos relacionamentos.
___
no aplicativo, o usuário poderá configurar os seus limites de consentimento e as suas preferências sexuais. 
___
com o perfil pronto, poderá enviar uma solicitação a qualquer contato do whatsapp, mensagem de texto ou facebook. 
___
o interlocutor decidirá se quer e como quer a relação sexual. o app permite que o internauta sinalize se autoriza ou não a gravação de vídeos íntimos, o uso de preservativos e de práticas sadomasoquistas. 
___
é possível também registrar uma garantia contra a transmissão de doenças sexualmente transmissíveis.
___

this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text: in 1993, lorena bobbitt cut off her husband’s penis with a kitchen knife. twenty-six years later, a new, four-part @amazon docuseries examines the misery and domestic violence that came before bobbitt’s notorious act. @thelilynews gathered a group of five women, ranging in age from 19 to 49, to watch and discuss the first two episodes. thirty-one-year-old viewer tiffany wang, a digital communications coordinator at ywca usa said, “the comfort with which young people talk about sex and consent and domestic violence and trauma, i think, is a marked improvement from what we saw in the video, and that’s something to be very grateful for. but also we need to be even more resolved to make change. seeing this, i was like, oh, nothing has changed with regards to domestic violence and the fact that it is a silent epidemic across the country.” (photo by amazon prime video; illustration by @thelilynews)

text:
я должна, ты должен....
мы должны
⠀
поговорим об обязанностях?
хочу привести несколько до абсурда очевидных утверждений:
⠀
убирать в доме- это обязанность всех, кто в нем живет.
готовить пищу- обязанность тех, кому она нужна.
растить ребенка- обязанность родителей.
⠀
есть и ряды других дел, которые по умолчанию  присваиваются женщине. но это не так.
⠀
вы наверное слышали или сами говорили:
-помоги мне убрать/ приготовить/ донести.
⠀
помоги ? как можно помогать с тем, если это его/ее прямая обязанность?
если и говорить о быте, то те, кто в нем живет, должны убирать вместе. или делите дом на 2 половины.
⠀
открою тайну, что ничего не делается само- постель чистая потому, что ее постирали; ешь еду- она не появляется на автомате;  оставляешь грязную посуду, а потом она хоп- и чистая такая на полочке.
я думаю, с этим понятно?
⠀
каждый в паре распределяет обязанности индивидуально и так, чтобы было комфортно и ему, и ей. и знаете,  гендерные различия здесь не причем.
⠀
я в детстве всегда убегала к отцу в гараж, мне там было комфортнее, чем с мамой на кухне. но по итогу,я так и осталась на кухне. сейчас я люблю это дело не только потому, что люблю, но и по тому, что нужно.
⠀
еще не понимаю фраз: нормальная женщина... настоящий мужчина.. . простите, а мы что, роботы, чтобы каждый соответствовал своим настройкам?
⠀
мы люди, мы можем развиваться в той отрасли, которая нам нравится. давайте не будем делить все по половым системам. запомните эту простую мысль. .
.
.

text:
sócrates e platão inauguraram o conceito de ética a partir de seus próprios atos e vida em sociedade.
___
mais adiante, immanuel kant, resgatou esse conceito e o transformou em “imperativo hipotético x imperativo categórico”, este último traz um questionamento que pode ser resumido da seguinte forma: 
___
“o que você faria se ninguém pudesse te ver?”
___
a resposta a essa questão vem no sentido ético e explica que a moral não deve ter condicionamentos, não deve acontecer porque alguém está de vigia, e que as suas decisões afetam diretamente ao outro e a sociedade. em outras palavras a ética só é possível se você tiver enraizado em si o princípio do respeito!
___
desta forma, enquanto o egotismo narcisista estiver acentuadamente presente, não é possível ser ético. 
___
reflitamos sobre nossos pensamentos e ações enquanto ninguém puder nos enxergar?
___
sejamos melhores pessoas para podermos ser melhores companheiros para os outros...
.
.
.
.

text:
você sabia que existem muitos app’s que oferecem serviços de condução apenas para as mulheres?
___
pois é, com um elevado número de casos de cantadas de motoristas convencionais nos serviços, como por exemplo, do uber, e até casos de assédio, alguns empreendedores resolveram criar aplicativos deste tipo de serviços onde os motoristas na verdade são as motoristas. 
___
isso mesmo, tanto condutores são mulheres, como passageiras o são. a maior parte destes serviços contratam mulheres para conduzir seus carros, o que também é uma possibilidade de emprego interessante em meio à crise econômica.
___
a proposta é trazer maior conforto e tranquilidade para o público feminino. 
___
as maiores empresas no ramo já estão se adaptando enquanto a cultura machista e a falta de educação de alguns bolsões da sociedade ainda não evoluíram para melhor...

text:
na real, foda-se o dia do abraço! 
___
o assunto aqui é o que você faz pelo outro ser humano? 
___
sabemos que o machismo gerou uma cultura da opressão sobre o outro, quer seja a mulher (que sofre a milênios), quer seja sobre as minorias e, quer seja sobre o o outro, inclusive o próprio homem.
___
minha proposta neste post é escancarar a deficiência que a narrativa da igualdade de oportunidades (diga-se, do respeito), pode assumir se utilizarmos o próprio discurso machista e opressor para combatê-lo. 
___
para fugir de um estado de fúria contra o próximo, proponho que se defenda o respeito como o princípio basilar nas suas atitudes e com isso fazer com que o discurso do feminino ganhe o seu devido lugar na sociedade.
___
o discurso de ódio pode estar inserido como um vírus que gera um efeito rebote nas suas ações. 
___
que tal uma mudança de atitude?
___
qual sua opinião?
.
.
.
.

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
my first collab with my fav @hijab._.writes ❤.. audio by;@musawiramotivates
caption by @hijab._.writes "mitti hoja mitti"❤
insan mitti sey banaya gya hai or mitti ajzi or inkisari ki nishani hai is lehaz se insan mein bhi ajzi honi chahiye magar haqeeqat is sey mukhtilf hai insaan mein na to ajzi hai na inkisari hai khas tor p un logo mein to bilkul nhi jo ajkl apney saath high status ka tag ley ker ghomtey aik barey auhdey p pohnch k khud ko khuda smjhney lag jatey or asal khuda ka khouf unkey dilo sey mitt jatta hai wo smjhtey k wo kuch bhi krey unka koi kuch bigar ni skta ku k yaha ka qanoon or adaltein to unkey isharo p nachtey hai...unkey liye insan zindigi ki ya uskey khoon ki koi qeemat nhi hai aik amer bap ka beta kesi gareeb ko apni gari k neechae dey ker chlla jatta hai to koi shour ni uthta ku mein pochti hon kyon ni uth ta kya wo insan ni tha jisko aik ameer bap ki biggri aulad ney rat k andhere mein nashae mein dhut gari chlatey hue apni gari key neechae de diya...afsos dr afsos k insaniyat ab hamarey ander baqi na rahi ab to salam hi usey kiya jatta jiskey pass koi auhda hotta...hyeee aik mitti se bnae insaan ko apni taqat pr kitna ghamend hotta ye jantey hue bhi k uski auqat sirf itni si hai k wo mitti se bnaya gya or mitti mein hi dafna diya jaye ga or chand din matam key bad bhula bhi diya jaye ga to phir mein pochti hon kis bat ka garoor hai jab mitti se ban k mitti mein hi jaana hai or jatey hue wohi libas pahen na jo aik gareeb k jism pr hoga to kya frq tum mei or us mei uski bhi 2 gaz ki qbr or safeed kafan or tumhara bhi...anjam dono ka hi aik hai or khuda k nazdeek dono hi barber hai...aj ka almiya sirf ye hai key insaan apni auqat bhool chuka wo bhool chuka wo jis khuda k samney aker ra us khuda ki mrzi k baagair wo aik qadam chal ni skta.

text: “i will not be silent” this piece is for #concealedrevealed @ywcaneks. after the overwhelming response i had to the “president” themed piece for this month’s challenge, i decided to expand that idea a little further. i have donated art to this cause for years- but this year i had a soul sister that needed the center for safety and empowerment’s services. that made it even for crystal clear in my mind how necessary what they provide is for our community. please consider attending/supporting the show april 6th. 🙏🏻💪🏻❤️ #metoo #girlpower #iwillnotbesilent #speakyourtruth #art #politicalart #womensart @blmckee
