text:
“supremo julga criminalização da homofobia a partir das 14h
___
após seis anos, ação do pps que pede criminalização da homofobia será julgada no supremo
___
seis anos após ser protocolada pelo partido popular socialista (pps), em 2013, uma ação que pede a criminalização da homofobia será julgada pelo supremo tribunal federal (stf), a partir das 14 horas, desta quarta-feira (13).
___
o texto, relatado pelo ministro celso de mello, prevê que tanto crimes de homofobia quanto de transfobia devem passar a ser punidos com o mesmo rigor aplicado pela lei atual do racismo.
___
na sessão, os ministros ainda devem definir se o supremo pode criar regras temporárias para punir agressores ao público lgbt devido à demora da aprovação da matéria no congresso nacional.
___
na câmara dos deputados, está parado desde 2001 o projeto de lei (pl 5003/2001) mais antigo sobre o tema e que dispõe sobre sanções aplicáveis a condutas homofóbicas.
___
embora 14 estados brasileiros já possuam algum tipo de sanção civil, como multas e perdas de licença, o crime de homofobia não está tipificado na legislação penal brasileira.
___
nos casos envolvendo agressões contra o público lgbt, o crime é tratado como lesão corporal, tentativa de homicídio ou ofensa moral, mas não é tipificado como crime de ódio.”
___
fonte: g1
.
.
.
.
#homofobia #homofobiaécrime #gays #lesbicas #simpatizantes #respeito #lgbt #projetodelei5003 #pl50032001 #metoo

[esclarecendo o post: são revistas simbólicas que representam espaços abertos para as mulheres. 
___
não é uma crítica do uso do corpo da mulher, uma mulher pode e deve usar e valorizar o corpo dela do jeito que ela quiser. 
___
o post se refere ao respeito atribuído as pessoas nas capas destas revistas e o porque atrás disso. 
___
playboy foi nitidamente criada para agradar os homens sexualmente, enquanto forbes é o ícone de sucesso em vários âmbitos de business/sucesso. 
___
tem dezenas de revistas de corpo seja de esporte, fitness, saúde, etc como tem dezenas de business tambem. 
___
estas duas revistas têm sim um peso diferente e significativos diferentes. 
___
mulheres podem usar qq roupa, vestir de qq jeito e apresentar o seu corpo na maneira e lugar que ela quiser. 
___
nem toda mulher quer estar numa capa, nem toda mulher quer ter um corpo de um jeito específico ou ter uma certa quantidade de dinheiro. 
___
o que importa no post é sobre oportunidades e respeito. 
___
qual é a versão masculina da playboy? se tem, duvido que 1% das pessoas a conhece em comparação. este eh o ponto.] ___
ser girlboss é ocupar espaços com autoridade, respeito, credibilidade e liderança, e acreditar que qualquer espaço pode ser seu, não só aqueles pré-designados para agradar o olhar do homem. 
___
por mais valor às nossas competências! 📸 @alinelacerda_bz .

text_retweet:
posted @withrepost • @artivistha
.
.
.
.
elaine caparróz, de 55 anos foi espancada durante quatro horas pelo advogado, lutador de jiu-jítsu,
vinícius batista serra, de 27 anos, com quem havia se encontrado pela primeira vez na noite de sábado, 16. 
___
o agressor foi preso em flagrante, depois que os vizinhos ouviram pedidos de socorro de elaine que foi espancada durante 4 horas seguidas e chamaram a polícia.
___
elaine está internada em estado grave na uti do hospital casa de portugal, no centro do rio de janeiro, e terá ainda que passar por cirurgias reparadoras. 
___
de acordo com o irmão de elaine, rogério peres caparróz, a empresária tem diversas fraturas graves, trauma de pulmão e dos rins.
___
homem que espancou paisagista por quatro horas já foi denunciado em 2016 por agredir irmão deficiente e seu próprio pai na mesma ocasião. 
___
quero levantar a hipótese que este sujeito aparentemente pode ter psicose. seus atos parecem ter um contorno totalmente fora do normal, como um verdadeiro louco. a própria descrição da vítima indica uma falta de motivo 
aparente. 
___
uma pessoa com psicose, pode ter visões, paranóias, alucinações que induzam a estados alterados de consciência e a agressões sem sentido.
___
claro que na maioria das vezes, as agressões, violência e assassinatos que vimos por ai são motivadas por motivos fúteis como ciúmes, interesse financeiro ou qualquer outro motivo animalesco.
___
porém, nesse caso parece algo fora do contexto mínimo. 
___
vale sempre o alerta: nunca leve estranhos para sua casa, sua família, etc, no primeiro encontro. tenha paciência para construir uma relação, ainda que seja apenas sexual, ou corra todos esses tipos de riscos. procure saber melhor do que os perfis (falsos) da internet podem oferecer.
___
pense bem, você que usa aplicativos para encontros, use critérios mais inteligentes para conhecer pessoas, tipo, a vida real!!!
___
cuidem de suas vidas, pois talvez seus “visitantes”, aquele/a affair pode ser um louco/a...
.
.
.
.
.

text:
não importa o quanto distante do seu raio de quilometragem, uma pergunta sempre vem à tona: “qual é o país que mais faz sexo?”
___
independente da quantidade, qualidade é sempre o mais importante. 
___
porém se pensarmos nas sábias palavras de aristóteles “nós nos transformamos naquilo que praticamos com freqüência. a perfeição, portanto, não é um ato isolado. é um hábito”, então há que se supor que frequência ajuda no desenvolvimento desta prática mundial.
___
vejamos o ranking extraído de uma fonte distinta e mundial - pesquisa da  sexual wellbeing survey da durex (preservativos):
___
1° lugar - grécia 🇬🇷
2° lugar - brasil 🇧🇷
3° lugar - rússia 🇷🇺
4° lugar - polônia 🇵🇱
5° lugar - china 🇨🇳
6° lugar - espanha 🇪🇸
7° lugar - itália 🇮🇹
8° lugar - suíça 🇨🇭
9° lugar - malásia 🇲🇾
10° lugar - méxico 🇲🇽
11° lugar - frança 🇫🇷
12° lugar - índia 🇮🇳
___
os gregos transam cerca de 17 vezes por mês, com uma duração média de 22 minutos e uma satisfação média de 51%. agora entendemos porque eles quebraram o país, quebram pratos, mas ainda assim continuam dançando felizes ao ritmo d zorbás... 😏😂 ___
os brasileiros vem logo atrás com cerca de 16 vezes ao mês, com uma duração média de 15 minutos e uma satisfação de 56% **porém como nós tupiniquins gostamos de contar vantagem, neste caso talvez seja necessário rever nossos a veracidade deste índice...
___
o fato é que tanto faz quem faz mais ou menos sexo, tanto faz o tipo de relação, hétero, homo, etc, contanto que as relações sejam seguras, protegidas, maduras, sem feminicídios, episódios de violência... ___
neste quesito, infelizmente, o brasil esta muito mal representado...
___
leia mais em: http://jornalportalsul.com.br/quem-faz-mais-e-o-melhor-sexo/
.
.
.

text:
you dig your own grave without even realizing. you unknowingly sabotage yourself. it’s a toxic cycle that continues over and over, and over again. we all have moments when we romanticize the past. there’s a beauty in our nostalgia. we like to just remember the good. we choose the best snapshots. it’s easier that way, to just gloss over the bleak parts. you ruin your future when you make the decision that the best is behind you. why? why decide that? that’s a pretty big assumption to make. life is an unpredictable beast. you might be shocked with how she surprises you. you ruin your future when you stop giving yourself the chance to be open. you have no idea what’s around the corner. it might be a disaster or a blessing. but there’s only one way you’re going to find out: by finding out.you ruin your future when you stop trying because you’ve already decided the outcome. i hope you, and i, remember that the future can be just as great as our favorite parts of the past. the future has unlimited potential and if we close ourself off to it, we will never have the chance to know how wonderful it can be. let’s not ruin our futures without even giving them a decent shot. ***photo by: @walterwbrady

text:
for those who have heard the all too common (and often minimizing) statement that someone else has it worse, i'm sorry! you matter. your pain is real.  and, you deserve empathy, love, and support. no matter what you're going through, you are not alone. reach out. share your story. be authentic.
❣
for those who can't identify with the pain of others, learn how to listen instead. sometimes offering support is more valuable than giving your opinion or advice.
👭

text:
friendship is born at that moment when one person says to another : “what you too? i thought i was the only one!” -c.s lewis

we have a lot of “what you too!” moments back when we were k-2 teachers at upis and up until now.  the weirdest probably is buying a barbie doll, recently, for ourselves even at our age (shhh...🤫) and our children are boys! (so no excuses, we just bought it because it makes us happy 😻). so it is true, friendship is about finding people who are your kind of crazy.

text:
a poem (and sort of declaration i wrote). link to website in bio
✨✨
so hard on you at times,
unforgiving when you slow down,
high expectations,
low praise
you are soft like you were designed to be,
forever changing, because so am i.
spectacular, resilient, beautiful, giving…
you hold energy, life and growth 
every muscle, every roll, every stretch mark
represents me.
all i can say now, is; 
i promise to continue to nourish you
i promise to care for you
work with you
and above all, 
love you in all your different shapes and forms ✨✨
poem by cheyenne donnelly
✨✨
photograph of isabelle estrin

text:
today in history: episode 7 -
on this day, in 17 b.c.(before crenshaw), jacob latimer of nethapolin discovered what would become the building blocks of modern society. it started out like any other day, kids roaming the poop pits, camels milking the neighbors, and women kneeling in formation when men approached. as the day went on however, jacob began to notice something was off. when he was using the women as steps to his bathhouse, he noticed one was missing. this was extremely unusual because it was his wife, step #6, that was the one missing. he summoned his servant, dillinger domingo, who was just a wee lad of about 7. dillinger searched far and near for her. when he finally found her, he could not believe what he saw. he reported it immediately to jacob, who was equally appalled at the heinous scene. she had been laying with the pigs in the mud pits. he shouted, “you’re silly, you’re lazy, and you’re gerfin!!!!!” thus the term slag(silly lazy and gerfin), was born, and to this day it has been upheld that all women are in fact, slags.
-

text: 2 years ago i was sexually assaulted on my way back to work. in broad day light, on a very public street. they never caught the guys because ‘the cctv was facing the wrong way’ and they left it ‘too late to take a e-fit’. honestly i haven’t really looked after myself since and wherever i walk my phone is in my hand so i’m ready to press the emergency button should it ever happen again. i urge everyone with a phone that is capable to set this function up. whilst i am fine, i have to see the place it happened every day and it makes me angry. i’m hoping karma will find its way to those 2 men. but at least i feel a little safer knowing i can press a button to alert my emergency contacts and emergency services should i need to. #metoo #karmasabitch #iphone #emergencysettings #girlpower

text:
"for as long as i can remember, i've been haunted by the feeling that "it's never good enough." #metoo 😵 i can relate to that sentence! i believe that is why #brenebrown books are so relatable to me! i am enough. it doesn't matter what your religion is, what your ethnic background, or what your sexual preference is, we all struggle with the feeling that "it's never good enough."
.
🦋
i was constantly trying to fill that void inside me. there was never enough alcohol or pain killers to fix me. they were slowly destroying my soul. i could read all self-help books, post all the inspirational quotes, try to fake my happiness, anything but get honest with myself. i didn't feel worthy of god's love, my husband's love, my kids love, the list is endless. i didn't love myself.
.
🦋
it wasn't until i was willing to get really uncomfortable that i realized that i was always good enough. god loves unconditionally. i was already enough. getting honest with myself, was an extremely difficult process but i can do the hard things sober. walking through my hurt was the bravest and most honorable thing i've done in my 35 years. being truly authentic and vulnerable is where the magic happens. happy friday! you are already enough!

doubt and the fear of change stop thousands of people from manifesting what they want. 
people look at their lives and worry about what might happen. the what ifs. 
life is like water. if it wants to move it's going to move. 🌊

manifesting what you want comes from an initial desire. from that desire, we create what we want in the mind. along this process, you can't have doubt. doubt starts to repel what you want. 
stay excited this beautiful world is going to give you exactly what you urn for. ❤️ a boyfriend or girlfriend, financial freedom, opportunity, travel, friends, material. 
if you trust in the flow of life. 
if you leave doubt and fear where it belongs.

you will find your power to create grows massively 💭⌛️ follow @jamesmalins

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

when a self proclaimed racist, xenophobic, maniac military officer is plotting to kill all your candidates, and trump says nothing, it should be clear that we need to pick a side. we are fighting a fascist, there’s no room for counter productive infighting. we can have a million theoretical differences, which intelligent and thoughtful people should be having during political discourse—this is exactly what we are trying to save. however, we are in the emergency room right now. this is triage time. we can all get together, have a cup of coffee on november 6th, and discuss the shortcomings of our democratic president and how we can shape their policies through political activism. let’s make america great, for once, and, for all. pick a side, there is a literal wall going up. it’s left or right—and you don’t have to be a republican (right) to be wrong. #unitedwestanddividedwewall. *

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said.
.
- the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
hey everyone! happy friday. i hope that you have had an amazing week. after a lot of consideration, i have finally launched my podcast. it would mean a lot if you take a listen. welcome to the first episode of the think unbroken podcast hosted by michael anthony. in this episode i talk about growing up in trauma in the midwest, falling into the vortex, the moment everything changed, and why i decided to start a podcast. this is the first of many podcasts in which i will break down my own experiences and how i transformed my life. the goal of this podcast is to give other trauma warriors the tools to find health, sustainability, and happiness.

links in the bio.

https://soundcloud.com/thinkunbroken/think-unbroken-podcast-episode-1

text:
#metoo புகாருக்கு விளக்கம் அளித்துள்ள பாடகர் கார்த்திக்

தமிழ், தெலுங்கு, மலையாளம், கன்னடம் மற்றும் இந்தி மொழிகளில் 3000க்கும் மேற்பட்டபாடல்கள் பாடி உள்ள பாடகர் கார்த்திக் மீது #metoo-வில் சில மாதங்களுக்கு முன்பு பாலியல் புகார் கூறப்பட்டது. வெளிநாட்டு தமிழ் பாடகி கூறிய புகாரை கடந்த அக்டோபர் மாதம் தனது ட்விட்டரில் பாடகி சின்மயி வெளியிட்டார் .

இதற்கு தற்போது தனது டுவிட்டர் பக்கத்தில் கார்த்திக் விளக்கம் அளித்துள்ளார். அதில் புல்வாமா தீவிரவாத தாக்குதலில் வீரமரணம் அடைந்த வீரர்களின் குடும்பங்களுக்கு ஆழ்ந்த அனுதாபம் தெரிவித்துள்ளார். மேலும், தனது மீதான பாலியல் புகாருக்கும் விளக்கம் அளித்துள்ளார். அதில் எனக்கு எதிராக ட்விட்டரில் பல புகார்கள் எழுந்தன. என் மனசாட்சிக்கு உண்மையாக நான் இதுவரை யாருக்கும் தொந்தரவு கொடுத்தது இல்லை. யாரும் பாதுகாப்பில்லாமல் உணரும்படி நான் நடந்து கொண்டது இல்லை. என் செயல்களால் யாருடைய மனதாவது புண்பட்டிருந்தால் தயவு செய்து என்னை நேரடியாக தொடர்பு கொள்ளவும். நான் மீ டூ இயக்கத்தை முழுமையாக ஆதரிக்கிறேன். யார் புகாரிலாவது உண்மை இருந்தால் நான் மன்னிப்பு கேட்க தயாராக உள்ளேன் அல்லது சட்ட நடவடிக்கையை எதிர்கொள்ளவும் தயாராக உள்ளேன் என்று விளக்கமளித்துள்ளார் கார்த்திக்... https://splco.me/tam/blog/2019/02/21/metoo-புகாருக்கு-விளக்கம்-அளி/ #metoo #பாடகர் கார்த்திக் #பாடகி சின்மயி #பாலியல் புகார்கள் #புல்வாமா #பெண்கள்

இதற்கு தற்போது தனது டுவிட்டர் பக்கத்தில் கார்த்திக் விளக்கம் அளித்துள்ளார். அதில் புல்வாமா தீவிரவாத தாக்குதலில் வீரமரணம் அடைந்த வீரர்களின் குடும்பங்களுக்கு ஆழ்ந்த அனுதாபம் தெரிவித்துள்ளார். மேலும், தனது மீதான பாலியல் புகாருக்கும் விளக்கம் அளித்துள்ளார். அதில் எனக்கு எதிராக ட்விட்டரில் பல புகார்கள் எழுந்தன. என் மனசாட்சிக்கு உண்மையாக நான் இதுவரை யாருக்கும் தொந்தரவு கொடுத்தது இல்லை. யாரும் பாதுகாப்பில்லாமல் உணரும்படி நான் நடந்து கொண்டது இல்லை. என் செயல்களால் யாருடைய மனதாவது புண்பட்டிருந்தால் தயவு செய்து என்னை நேரடியாக தொடர்பு கொள்ளவும். நான் மீ டூ இயக்கத்தை முழுமையாக ஆதரிக்கிறேன். யார் புகாரிலாவது உண்மை இருந்தால் நான் மன்னிப்பு கேட்க தயாராக உள்ளேன் அல்லது சட்ட நடவடிக்கையை எதிர்கொள்ளவும் தயாராக உள்ளேன் என்று விளக்கமளித்துள்ளார் கார்த்திக்... https://splco.me/tam/blog/2019/02/21/metoo-புகாருக்கு-விளக்கம்-அளி/ #metoo #பாடகர் கார்த்திக் #பாடகி சின்மயி #பாலியல் புகார்கள் #புல்வாமா #பெண்கள்

text_retweet:
we talked about birth plans this past week. this sums it up nicely. 😉 #empoweredbirth #evidencedbasedbirth #knowyouroptionsinbirth #birthmatters #repost @birthmonopoly with @get_repost
・・・
fixed it!  so from a legal and human rights perspective, my version is more accurate.  how on earth, then, do we have it so reversed??
.
for one, patients, providers, and the public are unaware of the rights of birthing people.  yes, all three of those groups.  most people believe that the doctor "ultimately" has the right to make decisions about birth.
.
obviously, this contributes to a lot of problems: skyrocketing induction and c-section rates, birth trauma and ptsd, and yeah, i'll say it--even more reinforcement of truly messed up cultural beliefs and norms around how women and mothers are valued.  which is to say, not very much.  the birth room is where prejudice, sexism, racism, classism, and all kinds of other -isms converge on individuals at their absolute most vulnerable.
.
how do we flip that on its head?  we start with education.  i'll tell you what, it pissed me off when i found out after the fact that i had always had the right to say "no" to an induction being pushed on me.  i always thought i would have advocated for myself that much more confidently if i had known just how strong my rights were and what they were based on.
.
doulas and birth workers: you are the front line for this kind of education.  if you took my class, you'd understand why i feel so confident saying: "hospital policies are really preferences.  birth plans are really policies." (p.s. i tag acog in most of these posts, just in case anyone’s listening.)
.
tonight is the last night to get this class at a great intro price--over 25% off.  you have until midnight.  so get on it!  bit.ly/birth-rights
.

text:
lieber unbekannter,
ich fand dich eben einfach ungeschickt. mitten auf dem weg stehen zu bleiben um deinem kumpel etwas auf dem handy zu zeigen. ungeschickt deshalb, weil es der engste punkt auf diesem gehweg war. deshalb bin ich ja auch fast in dich reingerannt; konnte grade noch abbremsen. (kann man ja eigentlich immer als fußgänger, alles halb so wild.) genervt hat es mich trotzdem, das hat man mir wohl auch angesehen. gesagt hab ich nichts wozu auch, ist ja weiter nichts passiert. aber mein genervter blick, der war wohl zu viel. den konntest du  nicht auf dir sitzen lassen. also brüllst du etwas lautes hinter mir her und als ich mich nicht umdrehe setzt du noch ein lautes „fotze“ hinter her. da hätte ich mich dann doch gerne umgedreht. ich hätte dir sagen können, dass mein geschlechtsteil nun echt nichts mit unserem disput zu tun hat. oder ich hätte dir sagen können, dass, wenn dir irgendein teil meines körpers ganz sicher immer ausweichen wird, dass das dann ganz sicher der eben von dir beschriebene teil meines körpers ist. ich hätte dich eigentlich gerne zur rede gestellt und gefragt ob du alle frauen so behandelst oder nur diejenigen, die wortlos dein verhalten missbilligen. ich hätte auch gerne gewusst, ob dir kein besseres schimpfwort einfällt. oder warum es ausgerechnet dieses wort ist, dass für dich soviel beleidigungspotential zu haben scheint. aber was ich eigentlich am liebsten hätte wäre das: nicht sexistisch beschimpft zu werden. im ernst. sag doch einfach doofe kuh. dann müssen wir beim nächsten mal nur noch über konfliktfähigkeit sprechen. baby steps, you know?
#metoo #sexism #feminsm #sexist

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
when we think about chanel, we think about something we want, idealized or some, hopefully, we directly buy it. chanel is aspiration. 
since we were young or since when we read magazines, chanel has been something linked to chic and elegant women. those are clothes and accessories that elevate your look at the moment. having a garment from ‘the maison’ makes you feel closer to those people whom we consider stylish. chanel definitely is status, it is not available to everyone, neither economically nor in others. by this we mean that few people can understand or appreciate the artisan work behind a garment, the idea of which part of the collection or why chanel reinterprets the piece . also, chanel is personality. after all behind each collection is the brand of a woman who was a pioneer in everything. she was a feminist before the #metoo and did not mind working and alternate with millionaires, artists or dukes but always vindicating her independence, in all aspects. chanel is a lot ofthings. so when you wear chanel, it's not just a garment. 
with karl, an era ends but another begins ... it has been the destiny that has made it re-directed by a woman?

coco could not be more happier. right hand of lagerfeld , @virginieviardoffical dominates like no one the aesthetic codes of the maison. if karl has designated her as an heiress, we do not doubt that she represents the spirit of the house better than anyone! we are expectant to see with what surprises us and to know about what we will dream. 
in the end, is not just trying to aspire to have. it is about trying to be (a chanel woman). #chanel #virginieviard #karllagerfeld #paris #french #ootd #cocochanel

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

tweet_full:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

text:
сильные женщины.
♥♥♥♥♥
сегодня утром  на улице я встретила женщину с маленьким реьенком, первоклассник наверное. как правило, на ребенке портфель в полтора раза больше его самого, плохо завязанные шнурки на ботинках и мать, тянущая его вперед по снежной каше. и все было бы ничего, если бы не вопрос ребенка:" я папа сегодня приедет? ". пока я ехала с ними в тралейбусе, они на свою учебу, я на свою, все думала: вот это сильная женщина. одна с ребенком, явно работает, судя по тому,как она отвечала на звонки в 8 утра и краю строгой юбки-карандаша выглядывающей из под  пуховика.
♥♥♥♥♥
на паре, кстати была на ней впервые, мне задали вопрос о моем отсутствии в начале семестра. не тушуясь ответила на него. рассказала о своих проектах, о том,что все пропуски имеют подтверждающую документацию. но дело в другом. одобрительно покивав, мой молодой и очень симпатичный преподаватель тихо, почти не слышно сказал:"сильная девушка"( внесу небольшую ремарку: в группе подавляющее большинство студентов-парни).
вот тут у меня в голове что-то щелкнуло. 
хочу ли я такое будущее? хочу ли быть сильной женщиной?
♥♥♥♥♥
ответ для меня оказался очевиден. я могу решить почти любые вопросы самостоятельно. но потрачу на это множество личных ресурсов. зачем мне это? ведь я могу просто поросить. ♥♥♥♥♥
девушка может позволить себе некоторые слабости. быть легче, нежнее и уютнее, чем кажется нужным. разрешать себе капризы. порой стоит специально потерпеть неудачу, чтобы привлечь свое счастье.

.
"kleiner tipp" – am arsch!
.
heute hat die mutti wieder ungefragt einen hinweis zu ihrem dasein erhalten.
ich wäre ja nicht alleinerziehend. papa ist ja da. papa macht. ich wäre maximal teil-alleinerziehend.
.
grundsätzlich hätte ich jetzt lust, zu pöpeln.
.
aber ich bin höflich und sage danke. ich werde das zukünftig berücksichtigen.
.
papa freut sich unter garantie ein zweites loch in den hintern, wenn ich ihn in meiner woche anrufe, weil ich
…krank
…müde
…lustlos
…pleite
bin. ich würde ihn dann wohl auch einfach eintakten, wenn ich
…wäsche wasche
…essen koche
…mit dem hund rausgehe
…duschen bin
…termine habe (insbesondere die mit kind)
…oder - schock! - mal dinge erledige, die ohne kind praktischer sind.
sollte ich dann auch mal völlig überfordert mit meinem heiß geliebten fleisch und blut sein, würde ich ihn easy-peasy spontan bitten, vorbeizukommen, um mir dabei zu helfen, das
...frustrierte
…schreiende
…unruhige
…traurige
…nervöse
…rastlose
…kotzende
…kackende
…allgemein übellaunige kind zu beruhigen.
und falls mir in manchen nächten 4h schlaf nicht reichen und das vielleicht seit eben genau einer woche am stück, frag' ich ihn auch einfach. kann doch 'ne matratze mitbringen.
und für mich hat sich ja so gesehen auch nichts wirklich verändert. außer dass ich tonnenweise mehr freizeit habe.
in der ich dann nach einem 10h-arbeitstag
…wäsche wasche
...die bude entkeime
…essen vorkoche
…mit dem hund rausgehe
…vor-duschen bin (super idee!)
…termine wahrnehme, die ohne kind einfach praktischer sind
…termine vereinbare, die zwingend mit kind notwenig sind.
.
okay. verstanden. trotzdem ein kleiner tipp:
zerbrich' dir nicht den kopf darüber, was ich bin und was nicht.
ich bin in erster linie mama. eine gute und eine oft sehr glückliche noch dazu. wie viele millionen andere frauen auch.
.
ich habe 14 tage im monat "frei" und könnte mir die sonne auf dem pelz scheinen lassen. richtig. das sind die 14 tage, in denen ich mein kind nicht bei mir habe. nicht weiß, was los ist. mein kind nicht sehen, fühlen, umarmen, küssen kann. ⬇️⬇️⬇️

text: september 2015 i surprised you all by posting hours before my emergency #brain #surgery that i might die but that i knew i'd be speaking to all again soon. it took some time but i kept my word. in 2016, i told you all i'm still adjusting to my new #invisibledisabilities but i'm going to push thru and start my #weightloss process that summer, even against my pcp advice. in 2017, i brought in the year 75 pounds down and counting, by spring i was certified in my first #zumba instructor course (#zumbagold) the same course that i started 10 months after becoming a #brainsurgerysurvivor. in 2017 i launched my umbrella company #visionaryv and told you all i would be expanding. january 2018, i signed my #dumbo lease for my #holistic #wellness suite and opened to the public on 2/15. was able to work on and get two new laws signed both taking effect this year, 2019. in addition, i collaborated with another organization and #visionaryvministries went on our first international #missions trip to #kingston #jamaica. now february 2019, i'm launching #visionaryvuniversity. still have my daily struggles, still sit connected to infusion machines one day every week but i'm here and thriving. i could be home on full disability and no one would question me but i wasn't ready to give up on my dreams and goals. i wasn't done serving my purpose. i wasn't ready to throw the towel in. i made a promise to myself one day after my #brain #surgery home alone on the floor crawling to the bathroom because my legs were too weak, that i wasn't going to let myself, nor my son down!!! might not be rich yet, however my word is my bond and that my dear is, priceless. someone is at their wits end but today i'm here to tell you to look past your pain and pull from your inner strength. - ms. v #yupstillblessedandverygrateful #ididnotsurvivebrainsurgerytoliveamediocrelife #thepowerofyou #blesseditbe #lifecoach #wellnesscoach #survivor #metoo #rapesurvivor #fostercare #singlemom #disabledparent #motivationalspeaker #keynotespeaker
name: Dr. V, Founder of Visionary V
tweet_full: september 2015 i surprised you all by posting hours before my emergency #brain #surgery that i might die but that i knew i'd be speaking to all again soon. it took some time but i kept my word. in 2016, i told you all i am still adjusting to my new #invisibledisabilities but i am going to push thru and start my #weightloss process that summer, even against my pcp advice. in 2017, i brought in the year 75 pounds down and counting, by spring i was certified in my first #zumba instructor course (#zumbagold) the same course that i started 10 months after becoming a #brainsurgerysurvivor. in 2017 i launched my umbrella company #visionaryv and told you all i would be expanding. january 2018, i signed my #dumbo lease for my #holistic #wellness suite and opened to the public on 2/15. was able to work on and get two new laws signed both taking effect this year, 2019. in addition, i collaborated with another organization and #visionaryvministries went on our first international #missions trip to #kingston #jamaica. now february 2019, i am launching #visionaryvuniversity. still have my daily struggles, still sit connected to infusion machines one day every week but i am here and thriving. i could be home on full disability and no one would question me but i wasn't ready to give up on my dreams and goals. i wasn't done serving my purpose. i wasn't ready to throw the towel in. i made a promise to myself one day after my #brain #surgery home alone on the floor crawling to the bathroom because my legs were too weak, that i wasn't going to let myself, nor my son down!!! text:
(delhi, india)
“i was sexually assaulted, and for a really long time, i chose to not talk about it. but when i eventually gathered up the courage to tell my friends, i realized something that shocked me. my male friends had been assaulted too. and that truly saddened me. i was surprised at how toxic and vulnerable masculinity can be at the same time. isn’t that ironic? but then most of the old rules we follow are just that. we’ve been conditioned to believe that only women are victims. that’s why i started making art on this. hopefully, if i do it enough, i can someday make it okay for a man to admit that he is a survivor, not a victim. just like i did.”

to the fellow who told me i was “overreacting,” when explaining my truth regarding a male predator, this is for you and every woman who has fallen prey to his (this) destructive behaviour. this is not meant to break you down, but build you up. breakdown and breakthrough. 
#wegotthis #metoo .
.

text:
if you feel pain where the tendon (medial epicondyle) attaches to the inside of the elbow – that bumpy part that tingles when we knock it. chances are you are experiencing golfer elbow 🏌️‍♂️ .
the main symptoms of golfers elbow are pain and tenderness around the bony bit on the inside of the elbow called the medial epicondyle, particularly when gripping hard with the hand. it is also not unusual to experience a general weakness in our wrists, with pain occurring when bending our wrist palm downwards against any resistance.
.
initially, the pain and inflammation can be relieved though the use of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs such as ibuprofen or aspirin while applying the p.o.l.i.c.e principle;

protection – protect the forearm / elbow / wrist from being aggravated further.
.
optimal loading – this means that rather than resting the elbow and waiting, recovery can be sped up by using the muscles affected at a restricted level to help stimulate the cells in the recovery process. this always prevents the muscles from weakening and shortening.
.
ice – use ice immediately after the injury occurs to prevent inflammation.
compression – the use of a support or taping will help compress the affected area, immobilising and protecting it also.
.
elevation – elevate the hand /arm immediately to reduce pain and blood flow to the injured area.
should your injury worsen over time or continue to cause you issues, 
physiotherapy is encouraged.
.
do tag your friends who might be experiencing the same too 
#golfelbow #golferelbow #elbowpain #elbow #medialepicondyle #metoo #value

-unnecessary familiarity, such as deliberately brushing up against someone
-insults or taunts of a sexual nature

text:
аптечка для новорожденного

ребёнок требует постоянного ухода, и подготовка аптечки является очень важным моментом☝🏼
⠀
мне написала девушка с просьбой опубликовать письмо в рубрике «беременный совет», что я конечно же и делаю💁🏻‍♀️
⠀
«всем привет! меня зовут настя) сейчас активно готовлюсь к встречи с малышом) изучив интернет, составила список того, что необходимо в аптечке для новорождённого. девочки, может что-то нужно исключить или что-то добавить? посоветуйте!

средства гигиены
📌жидкое мыло или гель для купания малыша
📌детский крем
📌крем от опрелостей (бепантен). его может использовать мама при лечении трещин на сосках.
📌присыпка
📌вата для чистки ушек и носика
📌обычные ватные палочки (для обработки пупочной раны и тд)
📌ватные палочки с ограничителем (для очищения ушной раковины)
📌ватные диски
📌детские влажные салфетки
📌бинт стерильный для обработки ссадин, царапин
⠀
продолжение листайте ➡️
name: Бортики ✨Текстиль

text:
dit mooie boek haalde ik deze week weer uit de kast om verder te lezen. ik begon erin bij het ecodorp aardehuis vlak voor nieuwjaar 2018. afgelopen jaar heb ik het boek er geregeld bij gepakt. 👉🏻maya angelou: "iedereen die kan lezen, zou dit boek moeten lezen."
🌎 hoe meer ik me in de materie verdiep, hoe meer ik me realiseer dat er nog vele 'ongetemde' schatten aan wijsheid te ontdekken zijn... dit boek heeft vele vrouwen geraakt. en via hen ook mannen, in het dagelijkse leven, dat weet ik zeker. het boek zelf is niet zo transformerend maar wanneer je daadwerkelijk bepaalde routines en rituelen in je leven integreert, wordt het different. 
er zijn (ook in nederland) diverse succesvolle ondermemersgroepen actief die vanuit een sisterhood openheid een sociale shift creeren. ik heb kosteloos aan enkele masterclasses met geleide meditaties deelgenomen. eye openers! 
de relatie tussen mind, body en earth/space staat centraal. het is een wonderlijke tijd, wow. ook relevant t.a.v.  diversiteitsbeleid, mixed genders en economie, want empathie speelt in deze beweging een krachtige en geen ondergesneeuwde rol. en doordat vrouwen helder vanuit hun hart handelen hebben mannen een duidelijker beeld van hun wensen en mogelijkheden. 💛💥 samen maken we een einde aan machtsmisbruik en daar bloeit de samenleving van! #metoo not anymore! er is een beweging ondernemers opgestaan die (ook met mannen) van binnen uit een verschil wil maken. 
vier de rijkdom van de natuur, connect met je essentie en neem van daaruit actie. dat is duurzaam ondernemerschap, geleid door je hart en wederzijdse understanding. met omzet en impact; laat beperkende overtuigingen los. en zet je 'oerangsten' via acceptatie, om in daadkracht. je angsten recht aan durven kijken, dat is de crux

text:
recently a lot has changed very quickly. 
i found out someone i once deeply feared now keenly monitors everything i post online, when it used to be the other way around. 
after the shock of knowing i have my first fan as a budding writer passed, i realised that while it’s an unnerving role reversal, it also shows me i have actually come a long way. 
proving this, today i signed a contract for a dream job!
before everything™ happened work was equal parts vocation and obligation. but now that i’ve experienced what being out of action feels like, even the most basic campaign task is the most exciting thing in the world. 
i start in just over a week. 
i cannot wait.
#surviving #trauma #ptsd #rapevictim #rapesurvivor #metoo #ibelieveher #womenswave

text:
nun habe ich mir mein eigenes bild gemacht. und, um es gleich vorwegzunehmen, überzeugt hat mich leider keiner der beiden erzählbände, die unlängst kurz hintereinander auf deutsch erschienen sind. 
die titelgebende story #catperson von #kristenroupenian (aus dem amerikanischen von nella beljan und friederike schilbach), sie handelt von einer studentin, die den richtigen moment verpasst, ‚nein‘ zu einem one-night-stand mit ihrem date zu sagen, bringt präzise auf den punkt, was als topos des #metoo-zeitalters immer wieder auftaucht. sicherlich nicht umsonst war sie - nach veröffentlichung im ‚new yorker‘ 2017 - das erste stück literatur, das jemals viral gegangen ist und millionenfach in den sozialen netzwerken geteilt wurde. roupenian hat in dieser geschichte einem gefühl raum gegeben, das viele frauen kannten, aber nicht benennen konnten: „(...) der gedanke daran, was es an aufwand bedeuten würde, jetzt zu stoppen, was sie in bewegung gesetzt hatte, war überwältigend.“
was dann aber darum herum zusammengezimmert wurde, um den, wie man munkelt, siebenstelligen buchvertrag zu erfüllen, sind irgendwie geartete horrorgeschichten, die schockieren wollen, um des schockmoments willen. fast ein wenig ärgerlich habe ich das buch schließlich weggelegt nach der letzten geschichte „die beißerin“, dazwischen oft nur noch quer-oder angelesen.

bei #carmenmariamachado #ihrkörperundandereteilhaber (übersetzt von anna-nina kroll) heißt es auf dem buchrücken: „literatur als brennglas weiblicher lebensrealitäten“. dieses debüt ende 2017 im us-original erschienen, wurde mehrfach ausgezeichnet. hier war ich nach der ersten wirklich starken, eindringlichen, auch erzähltechnisch interessanten story „der extrastich“ sehr angetan. überhaupt kommt machado literarisch sehr viel ausgefeilter daher als roupenian. doch mit weiterem verlauf der lektüre wurde mir das alles zu krude, zu gruselig. mag sein, dass dieses gemenge aus science-fiction, horror, fantasy, fabel, komik und groteske auch einfach nicht meine art von literatur ist. 
den hype kann ich jedenfalls in beiden fällen nicht nachvollziehen.

text:
our post is still blowing up, so we've posted this image as the most common arguments by rape apologists on the thread are that she, greta, "doesn't appear to be resisting", isn't flailing or trying to push the man off, and that she looks fine. all common arguments used to dismiss sexual assault survivors today, many of whom have been in greta's position or similar positions. people say we shouldn't bother talking about anything serious concerning this image because greta brushed it off later in life, as if that magically erases what takes place in this and three other photos of the same event. 
this begs the question, why do people so badly want people to be okay with what took place in this photo. they so badly want people to not view it as sexual assault, even though it so clearly is an image of sexual assault.do they have a guilty conscience, maybe? it's no shocker that many of these people are cishet men and white women in their early 30's to 60's. they like to take the easy route and cite the time period or blame the #metoo movement. not a day goes by where some incel or trumpette finds a reason to attack the #metoo movement. there's something more going on with these people who are so eager to keep the romantic ideal of this problematic image. 
just because sexual assault was normalized in the 40's and not discussed in depth like it is today, does not mean we should sweep history under the rug. it is not okay, and there is no excuse, to grab a person and force yourself on them. it doesn't matter if you wear a uniform or plain clothes, if you know them or just looked at them once. no one is entitled to another person's body.

text:
俠妹的多元選修課程上線啦❤️❤️每周五同步更新精華重點!!👏👏
👉🏻課程名稱：權力遊戲
course title: game of powers 
探討社會中各種權力面向中的不平等
👉🏻今日主題：流行娛樂文化中的女權
today’s topic: feminist in pop culture
女權抗爭是一部血淚史，至今仍然持續，在2018沙烏地阿拉伯才開放女性駕駛的今日，好萊塢女星也有同工不同酬、性騷擾的問題，而91屆的奧斯卡獎中，男性提名次數足足多了女性一千次，更不要說影視圈中女性形象長期是「花瓶」、「胸大無腦」，負責在電影中尖叫以及被拯救，是一個被觀看的客體，而喪失自我的主體性。
即使現今冰雪奇緣中的艾莎開始從公主「被拯救」到「拯救」，一枝獨秀的神力女超人至今穿著神奇的性感鎧甲(為什麼鋼鐵人不只包重要部位就好？蜘蛛人不能穿著緊身內褲在紐約飛來飛去嗎？)
李奧納多狄卡皮歐交了無數女友，被稱為「情場浪子」，泰勒絲卻被說成是「破麻」？這個社會是否至今恐懼女性的情慾展現？
韓國女團18禁性感舞蹈，該抨擊的應是「過於情色不檢點」，還是「不該只滿足男性觀看的慾望」？
👉🏻推薦mv：
lady gaga - til it happens to you
colbie caillat - try
katy perry - part of me 
taylor swift - look what you made me do
beyoncé - if i were a boy 
stellar (스텔라) - vibrato

探討社會中各種權力面向中的不平等
👉🏻今日主題：流行娛樂文化中的女權
today’s topic: feminist in pop culture
女權抗爭是一部血淚史，至今仍然持續，在2018沙烏地阿拉伯才開放女性駕駛的今日，好萊塢女星也有同工不同酬、性騷擾的問題，而91屆的奧斯卡獎中，男性提名次數足足多了女性一千次，更不要說影視圈中女性形象長期是「花瓶」、「胸大無腦」，負責在電影中尖叫以及被拯救，是一個被觀看的客體，而喪失自我的主體性。
即使現今冰雪奇緣中的艾莎開始從公主「被拯救」到「拯救」，一枝獨秀的神力女超人至今穿著神奇的性感鎧甲(為什麼鋼鐵人不只包重要部位就好？蜘蛛人不能穿著緊身內褲在紐約飛來飛去嗎？)
李奧納多狄卡皮歐交了無數女友，被稱為「情場浪子」，泰勒絲卻被說成是「破麻」？這個社會是否至今恐懼女性的情慾展現？
韓國女團18禁性感舞蹈，該抨擊的應是「過於情色不檢點」，還是「不該只滿足男性觀看的慾望」？

text:
@ekgkurvan fick ett hyperakut te-sug lagom till fredagsfrukosten! 🍵

dagens allvar som @ekgkurvan kommer tjata om många gånger framöver är att lära er känna igen hyperakuta t-vågor! att man ska titta extra noga på st-sträckan vid bröstsmärta och att st-höjningar i kombination med bröstsmärta tyder på en akut kranskärlsocklusion vet de flesta, men den stackars t-vågen blir allt för ofta bortglömd.. problemet med hyperakuta t-vågor är att definitionen är lite flytande, men tänk så här: 1) har patienten framför dig ont i bröstet? 2) finns det bredbasiga t-vågor som är nästan lika höga eller t.o.m. högre än  föregående qrs-komplex (”feta t”)? om svaret är ja på dessa två frågor så har du sannolikt en patienten med  en akut kranskärlsocklusion framför dig! ta ett nytt ekg (patienten kan ha hunnit utveckla en fulminant stemi under tiden du funderat på vilken sida som är upp på ekgt) och/eller slå en pling till din lokala pci-operatör som nog mer än gärna skippar teet i en sådan situation.

text:
•trigger warning ⚠️• („poetry slam - missbrauch) „es war doch nur ein  spiel“ 
er brachte mich zum schweigen, ohne es zu verlangen. er tat es ohne auf mich oder meine gefühle zu achten. er berührte ohne zu fragen. er ignorierte, dass ich es noch nicht verstand. es war doch nur ein „spiel“. ich fiel drauf rein. jahre später erkannte ich was er eig getan hatte. und nicht nur er. kleinigkeiten von 2 andern. es veränderte mich, meine zukunft. ich wurde krank. er hat sich dafür nicht interessiert. und ich hätte nicht gedacht das er das macht. wir kannten uns zu gut. du hast mich geliebt und doch so sehr gehasst. ich habe dir vertraut. du warst der einzige der da war und hast meine naivität ausgenutzt. jetzt tust du als wäre es nie passiert. und ich fange jetzt an zu realisier‘n. und sie hat‘s sich fast gedacht. denn du hast noch mehr getan. doch ich rede alles schön. mein mund ist verstummt. mit einer blume die es schön redet. es war schließlich doch nur ein spiel... hast du gesagt. ich kann dich nicht hassen , und das tut weh. denn ich konnte mich immer auf dich verlassen. aber sollte ich dich hassen ? 
du bist gegangen und wir haben abstand gewonnen. aber weißt du was du mir angetan hast ? was es für mich jetzt bedeutet ? - ich bin krank. ich kann nicbt reden. ich bin kaputt. ich war wie tot. nur mit viel hilfe kann ich wieder anfangen zu leben. doch er brachte mich zum schweigen. und mein mund ist verstummt, mit der blume die alles schön redet. denn es war ja nur ein „spiel“... hast du gesagt.... #missbrach#borderline#trigherwarninh#poetryslam#poetry#gedanken#depressionen#psycho#mentalillness#metoo#

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
sosok kevin halim menarik perhatian kami saat ia menjadi salah satu pembicara di acara seminar kekerasan seksual di dunia kerja yang diadakan oleh perempuan mahardhika dalam rangaikan 16 hari anti kekerasan terhadap perempuan tahun 2018 lalu. tim never okay project kemudian berkesempatan untuk berbincang dengan kevin halim, seorang transpuan berusia 27 tahun yang saat ini bekerja sebagai trans deputy program untuk gaya warna lentera indonesia atau yang biasa disebut gwl ina.

pada pertemuan ini, kevin menceritakan seputar pekerjaannya dan perhatiannya terhadap komunitas transgender yang harus menghadapi tantangan tersendiri di dunia kerja. kevin juga membagikan pendapatnya kepada kami mengenai pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja.

#sayneverokay #neverokayproject #metoo #gerakbersama

text:
‘to be a man’: a portrait series challenging the concept of toxic masculinity.
.
alberto. spain. "its okay for me to disagree with the classic stereotype of what it means to be a "gentleman". among the many, there is a very romanticised ideal of gentlemen and how they are meant to behave that exists and it is even imposed on men by some women. i am not saying i disagree with being polite and respectful but with how we are expected to conduct ourselves in certain situations. for example, the idea that men must earn more, be more responsible and hold higher positions to those of women,  is not correct. this behaviour also feeds into and creates gender inequality. men face a lot of pressure to live up to these very specific ideologies and if we don’t we fall short."
- visit www.jessicaamity.com for the full series .
.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said.
.
- the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
michael jackson estate sues hbo for non-disparagement contract breach

the estate of the late pop superstar #michaeljackson sued #hbo, claiming that plans for the cable network to air a documentary detailing ) child #molestation claims against the singer violate a 27-year-old contract.

the lawsuit claims that if hbo broadcasts #leavingneverland as planned next month, it would breach nondisparagement language in a pact that allowed the channel to show "michael jackson in concert in bucharest: the dangerous tour." hbo reaffirmed that its plans to air "leaving neverland" remain unchanged. the first installment of the four-hour documentary is scheduled to air on hbo on march 3, with the second half airing the following night. >
>>>read more at legalactionnews.com
>

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said.
.
- the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong

text:
julia jacklin is an australian singer/songwriter based in sydney, australia.

crushing, her second album, embodies every possible meaning of its title word. it’s an album formed from sheer intensity of feeling, an in-the-moment narrative of heartbreak and infatuation.  with her storytelling centered on bodies and crossed boundaries and smothering closeness, crushing reveals how our physical experience of the world shapes and sometimes distorts our inner lives. “this album came from spending two years touring and being in a relationship, and feeling like i never had any space of my own,” says the melbourne-based artist. “for a long time i felt like my head was full of fear and my body was just this functional thing that carried me from point a to b, and writing these songs was like rejoining the two.” #juliajacklin #australianmusic #singer #songwriter #metoo #newmusic #crushing #indiefolk #indierock #melbournemusic #sydneymusic

sie hatten als mitglieder der 1942 gegründeten widerstandsgruppe weiße rose in der münchner universität sechs verschiedene flugblätter ausgelegt, die zum widerstand gegen das ns-regime aufriefen.

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
card reading feb 21 2019

for carolyn ❤️ (and family) 
last evening i begin listening to krishna das, i haven't listened to him for about 3 months and this for me is spirits way of connecting me with your energy :) ... if i remember correctly i started thinking about listening to krishna das about a week ago, and i believe this was in preparation of reviewing your text message this morning asking for a reading ❤️🙏 i love how spirit works ☝️ "om namah shivaya"

when i started preparation for this reading i could feel a feminine energy and i visualized this energy as an elephant (veiled under face lace) also seeing shiva. 
i feel you have a connection with very ancient wisdom, and calling upon this energy will be of great benefit for assisting you in finding the relief you're looking for. i feel that at some level, conscious or un-consciously, you already know this.

i feel like whatever is grinding its teeth on you (figuratively of course) has been with you a long time, all of this life for certain but i feel like it's been with you before (past life, feels like last life) 
you are your inner child ❤️ card pulled 22nd and is card 49 in the sequence of cards.

ascended master retreats

i believe this card is coming up for you to remind you to call upon your faith for guidance along your path, to trust your inner child's direction. i feel a lot of energy around the word disciplined and i'm not certain how this attaches itself to you. 
each of us are on an individual journey of perceiving and through our perceptions we form what generally makes up our belief systems. it is important for us to remember that nothing can inject itself into our belief systems unless we accept it as our own.

i am being drawn into a strength you carry with you from this life time and a past life time. 
trust in the devine inner strength

find peace within

it is important to focus on self

each of us are on our own journey of learning and healing and becoming and by honoring this we give ourselves permission to forgive and forgiveness comes in many forms of acceptance, acceptance to understand the individualness of our own journeys.

more on facebook

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
【說不出口的遊戲。影評】真人真事！有血有淚！來讓一切說得出口！
李美
～
（注意，以下完全劇透，有雷）
～
《說不出口的遊戲》甫一開始便開門見山，講述小女孩odette（cyrille mairesse 飾）如何在所謂「little tickles」的「搔癢遊戲」下，遭常常來家探訪的父母朋友gilbert（pierre deladonchamps 飾）騙入洗手間內性侵。本片英文本名正是《the tickling》，國際版本則是《little tickles》。
～
香港將電影命名為《說不出口的遊戲》，比較原來版本某程度更加傳神。因為，這帶出「說不出口」的重點，既呼應了電影海報裡小女孩封口的含意，也凸顯出#metoo重在「說出口來」－－由andréa bescond親自飾演的成年版odette，不單在戲裡指證告發gilbert，現實的她甚至將個人不幸拍成舞台劇及電影，從而以身作則呼籲大家勇於面對性侵。始終，性罪行者一方面必須就自己所作之惡伏法，而另一方面，交付法律制裁也有助避免更多受害人出現。相對台版譯作《不能說的遊戲》，這裡的「不能」就不太準確了，女主角絕對「能夠」並絕對應該「說出口來」！
～
要「說出口來」揭發性侵，亦即宣揚#metoo的舉報精神，本片就很好透過多位要角來深刻探討。
～
對odette而言，心理醫生（carole franck飾）無疑是最終的催化劑，她便是odette第一個敢於突破自己、道出性侵真相的對象。
～
不過，追本溯源，odette父母豈不應該才是知悉真相的第一人？香港政府宣傳說「聽聽少年心底夢」，媽媽mado（karin viard飾）就更應「聽聽少女心底話」；若非她的虎媽性格、「有佢講無人講」不聽女兒說話，試問gilbert又怎會一而再得逞？也莫說，這位媽媽最後尚且「blame the victim」亦即「責備受害人」，居然認為長大後的odette不應該指控gilbert......至於爸爸fabrice（clovis cornillac飾）縱然是位慈父，但「有心做好事」不等於「真箇做好事」；在得悉真相後，他就對當日自己的「無能」內疚非常，甚至遺憾地說自己必須「躲進藉口裡」......這對父女在車上真情流露的一幕，絕對是電影的一大催淚位，相信每位家長都會深切感受到那種無奈與悔恨。然而，除了父親的「白臉」演繹動人，「黑臉」母親之使人扼腕，特別她在警署前和見心理醫生的兩幕，其「激動人心」的厭惡演出也深值稱讚，兩位演員皆極之出色。雖不知道，現實中andréa bescond的父母是否同個樣子，但無論如何，兩個黑白互襯的人設及演繹，於情理兩方面都大大完善了「以戲載道」的#metoo探討。
～
再說odette戲中兩位男伴，一個是青梅竹馬的損友manu（gringe 飾），一個是正經八百的醫生戀人lenny（grégory montel 飾），他倆也在#metoo事件裡有著重要地位。首先，odette的女性朋友不少，畢竟舞蹈員身份令她周遭圍繞女性，可是，對於自己曾遭性侵，odette卻沒太多向女性朋友透露－－這是否意味，女性跟女性在#metoo方面更難啟齒？而男性則對性侵更加咬牙切齒？（fabrice和manu俱揚言要殺了gilbert。）確然，換在manu面前，odette似乎才更自在、更有安全感，除了敢於坦言遭人性侵，她還會走進他正在撒尿的男廁......此外，manu亦象徵了odette過去的夢想；她去探監並跟manu一起到美國，相關「超現實」畫面便說明了manu如何有助odette釋懷，他肯定是她的精神減壓藥－－當然，她的精神減壓藥還包括毒品......相對地，lenny則象徵了未來的夢想：odette能否跟平凡的他一起到老？其實等於說odette能否返回正常人的生活與心境。本來，odette希望的是lenny適應自己的生活模式，不願反過來投進他的世界過活；但當舉報gilbert之後，odette才終於在百分百釋懷的基礎上，主動重返lenny身邊。可見，manu的心靈支持固然重要，odette沒有他肯定不成，但論程度卻只算治標；要真正治本，odette必須坦率面對自己過去，包括讓lenny接受真正的自己，否則她就無辦法走出陰霾、重見光明......（待續，劇透版二之一）
～
http://www.thinkhk.com/article/2019-02/22/33130.html
～
（影評全文，包括完全劇透的有雷部分，請瀏覽思考香港或facebook專頁，又或留意稍後的同片貼文）

不過，追本溯源，odette父母豈不應該才是知悉真相的第一人？香港政府宣傳說「聽聽少年心底夢」，媽媽mado（karin viard飾）就更應「聽聽少女心底話」；若非她的虎媽性格、「有佢講無人講」不聽女兒說話，試問gilbe又怎會一而再得逞？也莫說，這位媽媽最後尚且「blame the victim」亦即「責備受害人」，居然認為長大後的odette不應該指控gilbe......至於爸爸fabrice（clovis cornillac飾）縱然是位慈父，但「有心做好事」不等於「真箇做好事」；在得悉真相後，他就對當日自己的「無能」內疚非常，甚至遺憾地說自己必須「躲進藉口裡」......這對父女在車上真情流露的一幕，絕對是電影的一大催淚位，相信每位家長都會深切感受到那種無奈與悔恨。然而，除了父親的「白臉」演繹動人，「黑臉」母親之使人扼腕，特別她在警署前和見心理醫生的兩幕，其「激動人心」的厭惡演出也深值稱讚，兩位演員皆極之出色。雖不知道，現實中andréa bescond的父母是否同個樣子，但無論如何，兩個黑白互襯的人設及演繹，於情理兩方面都大大完善了「以戲載道」的etoo探討。
～
再說odette戲中兩位男伴，一個是青梅竹馬的損友manu（gringe 飾），一個是正經八百的醫生戀人lenny（grégory montel 飾），他倆也在etoo事件裡有著重要地位。首先，odette的女性朋友不少，畢竟舞蹈員身份令她周遭圍繞女性，可是，對於自己曾遭性侵，odette卻沒太多向女性朋友透露－－這是否意味，女性跟女性在etoo方面更難啟齒？而男性則對性侵更加咬牙切齒？（fabrice和manu俱揚言要殺了gilbe。）確然，換在manu面前，odette似乎才更自在、更有安全感，除了敢於坦言遭人性侵，她還會走進他正在撒尿的男廁......此外，manu亦象徵了odette過去的夢想；她去探監並跟manu一起到美國，相關「超現實」畫面便說明了manu如何有助odette釋懷，他肯定是她的精神減壓藥－－當然，她的精神減壓藥還包括毒品......相對地，lenny則象徵了未來的夢想：odette能否跟平凡的他一起到老？其實等於說odette能否返回正常人的生活與心境。本來，odette希望的是lenny適應自己的生活模式，不願反過來投進他的世界過活；但當舉報gilbe之後，odette才終於在百分百釋懷的基礎上，主動重返lenny身邊。可見，manu的心靈支持固然重要，odette沒有他肯定不成，但論程度卻只算治標；要真正治本，odette必須坦率面對自己過去，包括讓lenny接受真正的自己，否則她就無辦法走出陰霾、重見光明......（待續，劇透版二之一）
～

～
